\revision{Table~\ref{tab:ablation} removes one state feature at a time (Fashion-MNIST). Accuracy changes stay within about $0.35$ percentage points, so the policy is robust to any single removal. The largest drop comes from the battery feature ($-0.33$ percentage points), with latency and loss also contributing; removing the frequency feature raises accuracy slightly but lowers the Jain index the most ($0.78\!\to\!0.65$), so the participation features chiefly protect fairness. We keep all six features.}

